.\docs\packs\registry.json:40:      "description": "Defines resource types, economy profiles, and trade routes for the DINOForge economy system. Does NOT change vanilla DINO's default economy; this pack layers on top of it. Standard profile (economy-standard): all multipliers at 1.0x — a reference baseline matching default game rates. Starting resources: 200 food, 150 wood, 100 stone, 50 iron, 0 gold. Useful as a no-change anchor when combining multiple economy packs. Abundance profile (economy-abundance): boosted output for aggressive expansion. Production: food +50%, wood +40%, stone +30%, iron +20%. Consumption: food +20%, wood/stone +10%. Starting resources doubled (400 food, 300 wood, 200 stone, 100 iron, 25 gold). Storage +50%, building costs -10%, worker efficiency +20%. Trade rates +15%. Trade routes (8 total): 4 resource-to-gold exports (wood 10:1, food 12:1, stone 8:1, iron 5:1), 1 gold-to-iron import (2:1), and 3 cross-resource swaps (wood→stone 1.5:1, food→wood 1.2:1, stone→iron 2.5:1). All routes have per-transaction caps and cooldowns. These rates are pack-defined, not vanilla values.",
