"C:\\Program Files\\PowerShell\\7\\pwsh.exe" -Command "Get-Content -Path 'CHANGELOG.md' -TotalCount 15 | ForEach-Object { "'$_ }' in C:\Users\koosh\Dino\.claude\worktrees\swbundles
 succeeded in 295ms:
# Changelog

All notable changes to DINOForge will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed — SW UNIT bundles now carry real URP Lit materials (0 unit swaps → fixed)
- **Root cause (silent prefab-gen failure):** SW *unit* bundles rendered native in-game because their prefab materials referenced Unity's **built-in default/error shader** (`m_Shader: {fileID: 46, guid: 0000000000000000f000000000000000}`), which DINO's Hybrid Renderer V2 shader-guard rejects → 0 unit swaps. Three competing Editor builders existed; the dedicated unit builder `BuildSwMissingBundles.Build` resolved its source meshes via `AssetDatabase.FindAssets("<fbx> t:Model", "Assets/Models")`, but **`Assets/Models/` is empty** (no glTF importer in the project; the 44 `.glb` live under `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/raw/`). Every def hit `MISSING FBX → continue`, so the prefab was never regenerated and the build re-bundled the stale built-in-shader prefab (`Shaders 0.0 kb` symptom). Likewise `BuildAll.Run` only upgraded a material **inside** its `[skip] existing-prefab` guard, so all 75 pre-existing primitive prefabs kept their non-URP materials.
- **Fix (file+line):**
  - `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/BuildSwMissingBundles.cs` — replaced the `MISSING FBX → continue` silent-skip with a **primitive fallback** (Capsule) so every unit prefab is always regenerated with a URP material applied; build now exits 0 even when no real mesh is present (URP material is the load-bearing fix; mesh fidelity is a follow-up requiring a glTF importer).
  - `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/BuildAll.cs` — added `EnsureUrpMaterial(key, folder, color)` called for **every** def *before* the prefab-existence `[skip]` check, so pre-existing prefabs' materials are upgraded to URP/Lit in-place (prefab references material by GUID, so in-place upgrade is sufficient).
- **Verification (real, not "built N"):** Ran headless `Unity 2021.3.45f1` (one instance at a time, lockfile cleared): `BuildSwMissingBundles.Build` → `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels.Generate` → `BuildAll.Run`, each `-logFile`. `sw-shader-report.log` shows **19/19 unit materials = `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit`, 0 Standard**. The git diff of e.g. `sw-b1-squad.mat` confirms the on-disk shader moved from the built-in error shader (`guid 0000…f000…`) to URP/Lit (`guid 933532a4fcc9baf4fa0491de14d08ed7`, the URP `Lit.shader` GUID) with full URP material props (`_BaseMap`, `_SpecGlossMap`, `unity_Lightmaps`). Sample bundles rebuilt fresh: `sw-b1-squad` 23.5 KB, `sw-cis-aat` 23.5 KB, `sw-rep-clone-engineer` 47.9 KB — build log reports `Total compressed size 22.8–47.0 KB / uncompressed 103.6–152.6 KB` per bundle (NOT `Shaders 0.0 kb`). The `sw-rep-clone-engineer` prefab references material GUID `173ab220…` = its `-primary` URP/Lit material.

